{
  "text": ", where μ x and μ y are the means for x and y respectively. The Pearson correlation has a disadvantage of being sensitive to outliers [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The similarity measures explained above are the most commonly used for clustering continuous data. Table 1 represents a summary of these with some highlights of each.",
